182
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:40,670
我看见一个瘟疫面具
I saw a plague mask.

183
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:45,150
有点像中世纪医生 ... 在黑死病肆虐时期的形象
It's the kind the medieval doctors wore in... during the Black death.

184
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,460
你讲过类似的
You said something about that.

185
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:51,190
你在出租车里讲过 不过大多不连贯
You were talking in the cab it was mostly incoherent but...

186
00:15:51,210 --> 00:15:53,710
但我的确听到"面具"两字
But I did hear the word mask.

187
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,100
还有吗
Anything else?

188
00:15:56,120 --> 00:16:00,690
还有躯体 血液 火焰 ...
The bodies, the blood and fire and...

189
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,300
... 和地狱
... hell.

190
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,770
还有位女士
And there's a woman.

191
00:16:09,190 --> 00:16:11,540
那位女士 她看着 ...
The woman, she seemed...

192
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:13,790
寻找 就必寻见
Seek and find

193
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:16,500
呃 看着很吓人
Uh. Well, seemed so dangerous.

194
00:16:16,530 --> 00:16:19,240
不 你肯定有人我们可以联系一下的
No, you got to have somebody we should call.

195
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:23,030
我有吗 为什么
I do? Why?

196
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:28,380
我的 ... 我有没有
My wat... Was I wearing

197
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,550
在去医院的时候戴着块手表
my watch when I was brought to the hospital?

198
00:16:30,570 --> 00:16:31,990
没
No.

199
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:39,640
你没戴表
You weren't wearing a watch.

200
00:16:39,660 --> 00:16:43,420
它对我意义重大 是我父母送的
It's important to me. It was a gift from my parents.

201
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,980
嘿 你该朝前看 忘掉它
Look, you should go ahead and clean up.

202
00:16:46,470 --> 00:16:50,440
你的衣服沾血了 不过我想我有适合你穿的
Your clothes are covered in blood but I think I got something that might fit you.

203
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,830
你穿上后 我们就打电话给警方 行吗
Once you get dressed, we'll call the police, okay?

204
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:57,360
不 不 领事馆
No. No. The Consulate.

205
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:01,270
行 领事馆
Right. The Consulate.

206
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:08,970
咖啡
Coffee.

207
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:30,500
入读伦敦国王学院的12岁神童
Prodidy, 12, to attend King's College

208
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,770
伊格纳奇奥·布索尼 (昵称"小主教座堂")：我祈祷你一切安好
Ignazio Busoni: I PRAY YOU ARE ALL RIGHT

209
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,460
伊格纳奇奥
Ignazio?

210
00:18:01,340 --> 00:18:04,920
抱歉无法依计划与你会面
I'm sorry I couldn't meet as planned.

211
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:08,200
他们现在找上我了
Now they're after me too.

212
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,670
我们所窃之物
What we stole

213
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:15,160
藏于安全之所 本人亦是
... is safely hidden, as am I.

214
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,500
我们所窃之物
"What we stole"?

215
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:21,240
天堂 25
Paradise Twenty-five.

216
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,880
伊格纳奇奥
Ignazio.

217
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:48,640
你的东西我都放浴室了
I've left your things in the bathroom.

218
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,860
试试这些
Try these.

219
00:18:51,140 --> 00:18:52,880
这是谁的
Whose are they?

220
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,580
一位朋友的
A friend.

221
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:56,370
他住这吗
Does he live here?

222
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,530
有时候
Sometimes.

223
00:18:57,560 --> 00:19:00,010
噢 有时候 蛤
Oh. Sometimes, huh.

224
00:19:00,170 --> 00:19:01,790
你有点粗鲁了
You're being rude.

225
00:19:01,820 --> 00:19:03,120
抱歉
I'm sorry.

226
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:05,280
抱歉 我不是那种人
I'm sorry, I'm not like this.

227
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,190
那可说不准
You kind of are.

228
00:19:56,470 --> 00:19:58,850
我在旧夹克里发现了这个
I found this in my old jacket.

229
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,790
这是生物试管
It's a biotube.

230
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:05,340
用于运输危险物质
They're used for transporting dangerous substances.

231
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:06,930
你用来干嘛
What are you doing with it?

232
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,790
我不知道
I have no idea.

233
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:11,030
这是个高端装置
It's a high end unit.

234
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:14,200
官方制造的
Government issue.

235
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:18,710
这儿是指纹识别 万一遗失或被盗后的安保措施
It's called thumbprint recognition.
Security in case it's lost or stolen.

236
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:23,390
这种管子只能由某位特定人物开启
Tubes like this can only be opened by a specified individual.

237
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,530
这个 人肯定不是我
Well, it sure hell isn't me.

238
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:27,870
- 那你为什么带着它 - 我不知道
- Then why do you have it? - I don't know.

239
00:20:27,890 --> 00:20:30,040
我去查一下领事馆的号码
I'm getting the number for the Consulate.

240
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,960
请不要 等等
No, please. Wait.

241
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:35,220
我等过了 这样做不合适
I have waited. This isn't right.

242
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,800
你怎么会有它 你从哪儿弄的
Why do you have it? Where did you get it?

243
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:38,220
瞧 有个简单的法子
Look, there is a simple way

244
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:40,230
可以弄清楚它究竟是不是我的
to find out if this thing belongs to me.

245
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:41,940
我去用拇指打开它 或者尝试失败
Then my thumb will open it or it won't.

246
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:43,500
打开它 你疯了吗
Open it, are you insane?

247
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:47,000
如果它是病毒药剂 我打开后它会被释放吗
If it's a viral agent, will it be released if I opened it?

248
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:49,520
不会
No.

249
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:53,560
不会的 内部会有一层密封 甚至可能两层
No, there'll be an inner seal maybe even two.

250
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:57,830
把我自己交给别人之前 我想知道这是啥玩意
Before I put myself in anyone's hands I want to know what this thing is.

251
00:20:57,850 --> 00:21:01,170
嗯 还有我卷进了什么事件里面
Uh, and what I'm involved with.

252
00:21:01,570 --> 00:21:03,780
一切都合情合理 对吗
That make sense, doesn't it?

253
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:05,680
对的
Yes.

254
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:08,790
那么 达成一致
So, we agree.

255
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:11,280
我们把它打开
We're opening it.

256
00:21:32,070 --> 00:21:34,590
好吧 那说明它就是我的
Well, that explains that it is mine.

257
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:39,890
一个象牙制成的密封圆柱体
This is a cylinder seal made of ivory.

258
00:21:39,910 --> 00:21:41,350
不对
No.

259
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,900
这是骨头
It's bone.

260
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:46,740
人骨
Human.

261
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:52,040
三头带角的撒旦 正在吞噬三个人
Three-headed, man eating Satan.

262
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:54,810
中世纪时的常见形象
A common image from the Middle Ages

263
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,720
这与黑死病密切相连
associated with the Black Plague.

264
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,000
三张血盆大口
The 3 gnashing mouths are symbolic of

265
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:02,700
正是这瘟疫在人群中肆虐的象征
how effectively the plague ate through the population.

266
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:05,530
而你却记不起"咖啡"该怎么讲
Yet you can't remember the word for coffee.

267
00:22:06,690 --> 00:22:09,820
它在一定程度上解释了我的幻觉
It explains my visions, sort of.

268
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:15,080
- 你听见了吗 - 嗯
- Do you hear that? - Mm-mm.

269
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,820
可能是个法拉第指示器
This could be a Faraday pointer.

270
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:27,320
为 为什么会这样 嗯
So why-why this, huh?

271
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,050
波提切利的画作 (文艺复兴早期的意大利佛罗伦萨画派艺术家)
It's Botticelli.

272
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,140
这是他的"地狱图"
It's his map of hell.

273
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:48,880
详细描绘了但丁笔下的地狱 (但丁 - 神曲·地狱篇)
He painted it as an illustration of Dante's Inferno.

274
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:52,080
年轻的时候我学习过但丁的作品
I studied Dante when I was younger.

275
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,960
也许是在幼儿园里
Probably in kindergarden.

276
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,410
当时挺着迷的
I was a bit obsessed.

277
00:22:55,430 --> 00:22:59,480
但丁定义了现代社会中的地狱概念
Dante defined our modern conception of hell.

278
00:22:59,510 --> 00:23:03,700
我们对地狱的看法700年前就定型了
Our vision of it hasn't changed since he defined it 700 years ago.

279
00:23:03,730 --> 00:23:09,440
波提切利画了出来 但 ... 但丁是众所周知的缔造者
Botticelli drew it but... Dante created hell as we know it.

280
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:12,290
这也是我的幻觉所见
This is what I have been seeing.

281
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:14,490
酷刑拷问 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的献诈者)
Torment.

282
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:16,420
罪孽亡魂 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的挑拨离间者)
Sinners.

283
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:18,550
贩子被打上烙印 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的神棍)
Branding the mongers.

284
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:21,710
说谎者全身发疹 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的作伪者)
Liars, covered with rashes.

285
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:24,690
预言者头部倒反 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的占卜者)
Soothsayers with their heads turned backwards.

286
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:28,020
- 蛇 - 对偷窃的刑罚 (图为地狱第八层：欺诈的盗贼)
- Serpents. - The punishment for thievery.

287
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:31,650
受难吧 罪人们 为汝之孽付出代价
Suffer, you sinners. Pay for your sins.

288
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:34,380
那么你对为何拥有此物一无所知
So you have no idea why you have this?

289
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:38,890
我想现在或许该联系领事馆了
I think maybe we call the consulate now.

290
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:40,300
对
Right.

291
00:23:43,850 --> 00:23:45,200
兰登教授
Professor Langdon?

292
00:23:45,230 --> 00:23:48,290
你好 是的 是我
Hello, yes. Speaking.

293
00:23:48,310 --> 00:23:51,670
谢天谢地你还活着 我们一直在找你
Thank heavens you're alive. We've been looking for you.

294
00:23:52,070 --> 00:23:53,830
是吗
You have?

295
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:55,890
你还带着吗
Are you still in possession?

296
00:23:57,380 --> 00:24:00,490
兰登先生 管子还在吗
Mr. Langdon, do you have the tube?

297
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,510
- 是的 - 你的位置是
- Yes. - Where are you located?

298
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:07,420
教授 我们找不着你 就无法帮你
Professor, we can't help you if we can't find you.

299
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,920
如果那是领事馆 他们又如何知情
If that's the consulate, how do they know?

300
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:11,680
因为他们本就知道
Because they know.

301
00:24:15,010 --> 00:24:16,560
怎么办
What do we do?

302
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,170
告诉他们你在那儿
Tell them you're over there.

303
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:30,230
- 你好 - 教授 刚才断线了
- Hello. - Professor, we were cut off.

304
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:32,030
是的 抱歉
Yes, sorry.

305
00:24:32,050 --> 00:24:33,230
你在哪儿
Where are you located?

306
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:37,970
我在一家旅馆里 佛罗伦萨家庭旅馆
I'm at a hotel, Pensione la Fiorentina.

307
00:24:37,990 --> 00:24:40,590
待在房间里 我们的人马上就到
Stay in your room. We're sending someone now.

308
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:44,110
我在这等着 39号房
I'll wait here, room 39.

309
00:24:45,860 --> 00:24:49,440
好的 我们就等着 看他们派谁来
Okay. We wait and see who they send.

310
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:55,380
世界卫生组织 流动指挥车
清晨 6:37

311
00:24:55,490 --> 00:24:59,450
兰登通过佛罗伦萨的一个未加密IP登录了邮箱帐号
Langdon accessed his email account from an unmasked IP address here in Florence

312
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:01,460
- 什么时候 - 7分钟前
- When? - 7 minutes ago.

313
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:04,490
维亚多乐罗莎大道12号3C公寓
Via Dolorosa, number 12, apartment 3C.

314
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:06,260
维亚多乐罗莎大道 要多久
Via Dolorosa, how long?

315
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:07,200
12分钟
12 minutes.

316
00:25:07,230 --> 00:25:09,810
行动 拿回指示器 还有兰登
Go! I want that pointer back and I want Langdon.

317
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:11,460
无论如何 把他抓回来
Whatever it takes, let's get him.

318
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:13,390
走 走 走 走 就现在
Go, go, go, go, now!

319
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,940
看这个 好奇怪
Look at this. This is odd.

320
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:25,530
这块区域是但丁的地狱第八层
This area here is Dante's 8th level of hell.

321
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,820
叫Malebolge 意为邪恶之囊
It's called the Malebolge, means evil ditches.

322
00:25:28,850 --> 00:25:30,490
一共有十种罪恶
There's ten.

323
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:36,320
这儿的字母"R" 原画中并没有
This letter "R" here, is not in the original painting.

324
00:25:36,340 --> 00:25:38,150
是后加的
It's been added.

325
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:40,400
还有一个
There's another one.

326
00:25:40,530 --> 00:25:42,570
- 哪里 - 有个"E"
- Where? - An "E".

327
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,240
被恶魔鞭笞的诱奸者
On seducers whipped by demons.

328
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:46,720
- 面颊上有个"C"的人 - 是污吏
- There's a "C" on the cheek of a... - A grafter.

329
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:49,410
- 贪污犯 - 困在满池沸腾沥青中的骗子
- ... a grafter. - A conman trapped in a pool of boiling tar.

330
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:52,200
- "V" "R" - 啊 那儿
- A "V", "R".
- Ah, there.

331
00:25:52,230 --> 00:25:54,890
- "T" - 那儿 那儿 "A"
- "T". - There, there, "A".

332
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:56,860
那是什么
What is that.

333
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:59,280
一段文字 那是英文吗
That's text. Is that in English?

334
00:25:59,820 --> 00:26:08,660
唯有透过死亡之眼 才能瞥见真相
THE TRUTH CAN BE GLIMPSED ONLY THROUGH THE EYES OF DEATH.

335
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,030
佐布里斯特
ZOBRIST.

336
00:26:16,090 --> 00:26:17,750
贝特朗·佐布里斯特
Bertrand Zobrist.

337
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,990
- 美国的亿万富翁 那一定很棒 - 蛤
- American billionaire, that must be nice. - Hm.

338
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:22,810
生物工程师
Bioengineer

339
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:25,930
因激进观点而声名狼藉
Notorious for radical views.

340
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:27,490
他在这儿
Here he is.

341
00:26:30,350 --> 00:26:34,350
人类经历了10万年
It took the earth's population a hundred thousand years

342
00:26:34,380 --> 00:26:36,280
才繁衍出10亿人口
to reach a billion people.

343
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:40,960
在随后的100年 人口增长到20亿
And then just a hundred more to reach two billion.

344
00:26:41,130 --> 00:26:47,420
