距离午夜 我们还差一分钟
We're a minute to midnight.

357
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:40,550
每一次全球性的瘟疫灾难都可以被归咎于人口的过剩
Every single global ill that plagues the Earth can be traced back to human overpopulation.

358
00:27:40,570 --> 00:27:44,700
而严肃的生育控制手段却毫无施行可能
But serious birth control measures they don't stand a chance.

359
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:48,100
耸人听闻 违背个人权利
Outrageous! Violation of my rights!

360
00:27:48,130 --> 00:27:52,490
侵犯个人隐私 别来好为人师
Invasion of my privacy! Don't tell me what to do!

361
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:56,680
然而 我们仍在侵略自然环境
But still we keep attacking our own environment!

362
00:27:56,710 --> 00:28:03,210
地球历史上已经有过5次物种大灭绝
They have been 5 major extinctions in the earth's history.

363
00:28:03,700 --> 00:28:08,620
我们若不立即采取大胆行动
Unless we take bold immediate action

364
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:14,220
第六次就会轮到我们头上
the sixth extinction will be our own.

365
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:19,160
距离午夜 我们还差一分钟
We're a minute to midnight.

366
00:28:20,450 --> 00:28:22,390
看起来他有挺多拥护者
Looks like he's got a lot of followers.

367
00:28:22,420 --> 00:28:24,700
嗯 来自全球各地 五湖四海
Yeah, from all over the world.

368
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:29,500
他挺令人信服的
He is compelling.

369
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:34,620
在佐布里斯特消失的两年时间里 部分当局人员担心
The 2 year disappearance during which some authorities feared Zobrist

370
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:38,500
他可能研发了一种有害于免疫能力底下群体的病毒病原体
may have designed an opportunistic viral pathogen.

371
00:28:38,900 --> 00:28:41,250
他制造了一种瘟疫病毒
He created a plague.

372
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:45,800
但 为什么是但丁
But, why Dante?

373
00:28:45,830 --> 00:28:47,380
为什么是这幅"地狱图"
Why this map of hell?

374
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,370
这是拼图游戏 或者挑战吗
Is this supposed to be a puzzle or a challenge?

375
00:28:50,390 --> 00:28:52,300
也可能是遗书
Or a suicide note.

376
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:55,650
3天前他自杀了
He killed himself 3 days ago.

377
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:05,600
等级
The levels.

378
00:29:07,220 --> 00:29:10,430
罪恶等级是乱序的 这是困扰我的地方
The levels are out of order, that's what's been bothering me.

379
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:13,650
地狱这一层的次序被重新分布了
This circles of hell had been rearranged.

380
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:16,210
跟医院的女子是同一人
It's the same woman from the hospital.

381
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:19,650
我们不能待在这 肯定不能相信领事馆了
We can't stay here. We certainly can't trust the Consulate.

382
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,760
字母像布置时那样被加密 也不对
The letters are encrypted as committers, that's not right.

383
00:29:21,790 --> 00:29:24,230
如果病毒真的存在 你知道有多少政府想要弄到手吗
If the plague exist, do you know how many governments would want it?

384
00:29:24,250 --> 00:29:25,930
神棍 猜不出
Clerical profiteers, not there.

385
00:29:25,950 --> 00:29:28,070
- 他们都会做些什么来得到这些 - 挑拨离间者 不是
- What they would do to get it. - Someone who discord dead, no.

386
00:29:28,090 --> 00:29:30,130
生化武器
A biological weapon.

387
00:29:30,630 --> 00:29:32,200
这些字母
The letters.

388
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:38,410
他把每种罪行都加上了字母 然后打乱次序
He has assigned a letter to each sin and then changed their order.

389
00:29:38,430 --> 00:29:40,300
他设了一个字谜
He's made an anagram.

390
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:44,700
对了 字谜
Yes. Anagram.

391
00:29:48,730 --> 00:29:51,490
走 我知道另一条路能出去
Let's go. I know another way out.

392
00:29:58,340 --> 00:30:00,820
如果你带了手机 最好留在这儿
If you have phoned, best leave it here.

393
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:02,120
可能会被追踪
They might track it.

394
00:30:02,150 --> 00:30:05,830
手机 衣服都不是我自个的
The phone? I'm not even wearing my own clothes.

395
00:30:05,860 --> 00:30:08,630
很好 走吧
Good. Let's go.

396
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:21,050
罗伯特·兰登 世界卫生组织
Robert Langdon! World Health Organization! (WHO)

397
00:30:25,550 --> 00:30:27,740
V, R, O.

398
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:31,230
我得重排这些字母 Over Code
I got to rearrange these letters, CATROVACER.

399
00:30:31,250 --> 00:30:33,290
Covered Cat

400
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:36,250
天 这种东西我以前挺上手的
God. I used to be good at this.

401
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,430
Cerca trova.

402
00:30:43,150 --> 00:30:46,350
意大利语 意为"寻找"和"发现"
It's Italian. It means "seek" and "find".

403
00:30:47,110 --> 00:30:49,650
Cerca trova 好的
Cerca trova. Yes!

404
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,600
我知道我为什么会在佛罗伦萨了
I know why I am in Florence.

405
00:30:58,170 --> 00:31:01,190
世界卫生组织已经抵达 待命
World Health Organization has landed, standby.

406
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:07,560
注意
Be advised.

407
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:11,150
来自巴黎的布沙尔探员已经到场
Agent Bouchard, from the Paris office is already here.

408
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,270
世界卫生组织 告诉我最新情况
W.H.O, Bring me up to speed.

409
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:19,600
布沙尔已经上去了
Bouchard is up there now.

410
00:31:44,180 --> 00:31:47,940
- 我们去哪 - 旧宫 波波利花园附近
- Where are we going? - The Palazzo Vecchio, near the Boboli Gardens.

411
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,560
没有发现他
There's no sign of him.

412
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:06,120
布沙尔说兰登已经走了 指示器也不在
Bouchard says Langdon is gone and so is the pointer.

413
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:07,500
这可不行
Well, I need better.

414
00:32:07,530 --> 00:32:10,590
你 你 你们全部都要表现得更好
I need better from you, from you, from all of us.

415
00:32:10,770 --> 00:32:12,130
更像样
Better!

416
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:16,320
还要更迅速 更敏捷 别相信任何人
Work faster. Work smarter. Don't trust anyone.

417
00:32:17,130 --> 00:32:18,700
大家加油吧
Let's do that.

418
00:32:19,730 --> 00:32:21,490
- 去吧 - 是
- Let's go. - Yes.

419
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,950
情报看样子已经没用了
The information seems to be obsolete.

420
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:39,300
- 不要透露给秘书长 明白吗 - 明白
- Do not say anything to the secretary general. - OK

421
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:46,020
- 身份 - 瓦任莎
- Identification. - Vayentha.

422
00:32:46,050 --> 00:32:49,200
- 继续 - 我要跟教务长通话
- Go ahead. - I need to speak to the provost.

423
00:32:49,230 --> 00:32:50,690
稍等
Hold on.

424
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:54,500
亚得里亚海 (意大利东部地中海水域) 清晨 7:12
游艇"门达西乌姆号"
Adriatic Sea 7:12 AM
The Mendacium.

425
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:03,110
那么 WHO在追踪兰登这事上先你一步 瓦任莎
So, the WHO beat you to Mr. Langdon, Vayentha.

426
00:33:03,130 --> 00:33:04,680
教务长可不喜欢这样
The provost isn't going to like that.

427
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:07,240
我知道 他想要清掉我了
I know. He's going to want to liquidate.

428
00:33:07,270 --> 00:33:08,860
告诉他这儿不是柏林
Tell him this isn't Berlin.

429
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:11,110
他敢试 我就找上门
He tries anything and I will find him.

430
00:33:11,140 --> 00:33:14,270
一小时内再试一遍 然后联系我们
Try to reacquire and make contact in 60 minutes.

431
00:33:14,300 --> 00:33:16,630
你有没有在听 我不是一次性用品
Did you hear me? I am not disposable.

432
00:33:16,650 --> 00:33:21,630
瓦任莎 抢先将法拉第指示器弄到手
Vayentha, get the Faraday pointer before the government does.

433
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:23,180
靠
Shit.

434
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:47,740
- 西姆斯先生 - 嗯
- Mr. Sims. - Mm.

435
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:49,960
事情出了点偏差
There's been a deviation.

436
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:51,320
听到这个真遗憾
Sorry to hear that.

437
00:33:51,340 --> 00:33:53,490
- 什么行动 - 佛罗伦萨
- What operation? - Florence.

438
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:56,670
我们的新外勤似乎有点随性乱来了
Our new players seemed to have gone off script.

439
00:33:56,690 --> 00:33:59,600
真够业余
How unprofessional.

440
00:33:59,620 --> 00:34:04,620
现在WHO已经取代了我们的位置
And now the WHO has overtaken our position.

441
00:34:09,210 --> 00:34:12,080
告诉瓦任莎 如果她还在乎这份工作
Tell Vayentha, if she values her position

442
00:34:12,110 --> 00:34:13,890
她就该除掉兰登
she will remove Langdon.

443
00:34:13,910 --> 00:34:16,040
毁尸灭迹
Body not found.

444
00:34:16,060 --> 00:34:18,600
或者再妙点 拦路抢劫
Or better yet, a mugging gone awry.

445
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:22,320
来上一刀 我觉得 现金劫走 钱包留下
A blade, I think. Cash gone, wallet remains.

446
00:34:22,350 --> 00:34:26,920
赶紧确认下 然后继续 继续 继续
Let's have a quick identification and move on. Move on, move on.

447
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:31,850
兰登教授已经脱离监视了
Professor Langdon is out of frame.

448
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:40,540
- 还带着管子吗 - 是的
- And in possession of the tube? - Yes.

449
00:34:40,570 --> 00:34:43,040
他带着法拉第指示器
He has the Faraday pointer.

450
00:34:46,680 --> 00:34:49,540
之前盯的那么紧
He was such a good frame.

451
00:34:49,580 --> 00:34:52,980
- 瓦任莎的情况如何 - 无恙 但很焦虑
- What is Vayentha's condition? - Intact but anxious.

452
00:34:53,010 --> 00:34:54,600
那也正常
She should be.

453
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:02,190
这位委托人究竟都让我们做了些什么
What in god's name has this client gotten us into?

454
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:05,940
不不不 只是个 ... 比方
No, no, no. This is uh... rhetorical.

455
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:10,590
我们什么时候准备好发布委托人的视频
When are we due to release the client's video?

456
00:35:11,500 --> 00:35:12,690
视频刚到这
It just arrived.

457
00:35:12,710 --> 00:35:15,070
他的指示是24小时内上传
His instructions were to upload it in 24 hours.

458
00:35:15,090 --> 00:35:16,530
我现在想看一下
I want to look at it now.

459
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:18,160
但 委托人 佐布里斯特
But, the client, Mr. Zobrist.

460
00:35:18,180 --> 00:35:21,510
委托人 委托人已经死了 我要看视频
The client, the client is dead. I want to see the video.

461
00:35:21,530 --> 00:35:25,000
这是违约行为
That's a violation of our protocols.

462
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:32,490
我们不是政府 只是负责办事
We're not the government. We get things done.

463
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:34,360
阿博加斯特先生
Mr. Arbogast.

464
00:35:35,430 --> 00:35:39,600
能够令我们在工作中得心应手的首要因素
Chief among the attributes that makes us so very good at our job

465
00:35:39,620 --> 00:35:43,320
正是世人对我们存在的一无所知
is that as far as the world is concerned, we don't exist.

466
00:35:43,350 --> 00:35:47,100
倘若这段视频暗示或甚至提及到我们
If this video implicates or even mentions us in anyway,

467
00:35:47,130 --> 00:35:50,810
我就会基于客户权益考虑而中止其发布
I want to stop it's release. For the benefit of all our clients.

468
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:53,630
你要求过在流程操作中要避免异常事况 就这些
You asked me to avoid abnormalities in procedure, that's all.

469
00:35:53,660 --> 00:35:57,910
如果佐布里斯特先生当初只是在假装正常交易 怎么办
What about Mr. Zobrist has ever remotely resembled normal.

470
00:35:57,940 --> 00:36:00,760
- 那 我... - 也只是个比方
- Well, I... - Also rhetorical.

471
00:36:00,780 --> 00:36:02,550
把视频带过来
Bring me the video.

472
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:08,060
在旧宫(维奇奥宫)的五百人大厅内 有一副著名壁画
马基雅维利大道 佛罗伦萨 意大利 上午 8:36
In the Vecchio's Hall of the Five Hundred, there's a famous mural,
Viale Machiavelli, Florence, Italy 8:36 AM

473
00:36:08,090 --> 00:36:10,560
乔治奥·瓦萨里的"马西阿诺之战"
Giorgio Vasari's Battle of Marciano.

474
00:36:10,580 --> 00:36:13,500
在壁画顶部附近 有一段密文
Near the top of the mural is a coded message

475
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:15,320
这也是艺术界中最著名的未解之谜
which is one the art world's most famous puzzles.

476
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:16,710
密文是什么
And what's the message?

477
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:18,430
Cerca trova.

478
00:36:19,130 --> 00:36:20,950
寻找 就寻见
Seek and find.

479
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:23,090
在医院里 我一直念叨说我很抱歉
At the hospital, I kept saying I was sorry.

480
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:24,510
很抱歉 一遍又一遍
Very sorry, over and over.

481
00:36:24,540 --> 00:36:26,080
好吧 也许那不是我的本意
Well, maybe that's not what I meant.

482
00:36:26,100 --> 00:36:28,790
画家的名字 瓦萨里 我可能讲的是"瓦萨里"
The name of the artist, Vasari. I could have been saying Vasari.

483
00:36:28,810 --> 00:36:31,930
很棒啊 感觉你清醒多了
That's good. You seem clearer.

484
00:36:31,950 --> 00:36:34,530
- 是的 - 你的中间名叫什么
- I am. - What's your middle name?

485
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:37,490
呃 我挺清醒的
Well, I am.

486
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:39,330
嗯哼
Mm-hm.

487
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:42,490
佐布里斯特死了 但若病毒真的存在
Zobrist is dead but if his plague is real...

488
00:36:42,510 --> 00:36:47,440
那这幅"地狱图" 就是他留给某人找到它的线索
Then this map is a trail he has left so someone can find it.

489
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:48,950
谁
Who?

490
00:36:48,980 --> 00:36:51,890
嗯 跟他立场一致的人
Well, someone who believes the same as he does.

491
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,270
那就是你带着它的原因
And that's why you have it.

492
00:36:53,300 --> 00:36:54,920
但我印象中从未见过他
Well, I don't remember ever meeting Zobrist.

493
00:36:54,940 --> 00:36:56,960
你不记得的事情可多了
There's a lot you don't remember.

494
00:36:57,280 --> 00:37:00,560
也许他们 也许他们之前找到你
Maybe they- Maybe they came to you.

495
00:37:01,470 --> 00:37:03,090
征求过你的指引
Wanted your help with the path.

496
00:37:03,110 --> 00:37:05,080
- 就因为我做过但丁的讲座 - 正是如此
- Because I lectured on Dante? - Exactly.

497
00:37:05,100 --> 00:37:09,350
他们向你展示法拉第指示器 试着说服你支持那些主张
They showed you this Faraday pointer, tried to convince you of their cause.

498
00:37:09,370 --> 00:37:11,930
- 大屠杀 - 你说过他挺令人信服的
- Mass murder? - You said you found him compelling.

499
00:37:11,950 --> 00:37:13,520
那是指观点
His argument!

500
00:37:13,540 --> 00:37:14,900
口才
His rhetoric.

501
00:37:15,310 --> 00:37:17,550
绝非这些计划 佐布里斯特心理上有问题
Not his plan! Zobrist is a psychopath.

502
00:37:17,580 --> 00:37:19,090
好吧 或许他们耍了你
Well, maybe they tricked you.

503
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:21,720
其实给了 ... 你认识的人
Sent... someone you knew.

504
00:37:22,100 --> 00:37:25,030
离午夜还差一分钟
It's a minute to midnight.

505
00:37:31,330 --> 00:37:34,360
- 那是对付咱们的吗 - 常理来看是的
- Is that for us? - Logic would suggest.

506
00:37:48,780 --> 00:37:50,330
该死
Damn it!

507
00:37:52,110 --> 00:37:54,140
这儿 快 跟上我
Here, come on. Follow me.

508
00:37:54,170 --> 00:37:55,930
我们可以穿过花园到那儿
We could get there through the garden.

509
00:38:04,290 --> 00:38:07,880
好的 旧宫在这边
Okay, the- the Palazzo Vecchio is this way.

510
00:38:12,310 --> 00:38:15,920
过去一小时内 我们标记了她用信用卡购买的汽车
We just flagged the car charged to her credit card within the past hour.

511
00:38:15,950 --> 00:38:17,730
安托万 你跟警方交涉了么
Antoine, did you talk to the police?

512
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,800
那边有见过咱们的警察
There are people who have seen me.

513
00:38:19,820 --> 00:38:23,670
请跟当地警方合作
Please cooperate with local police officially.

514
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:32,240
WHO将负责监督波波利花园的搜查工作
W.H.O. will take charge overseeing the search at the Boboli Gardens.

515
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,870
把搜查犬调过来
Call in the search dogs.

516
00:38:37,900 --> 00:38:44,100
我在警局里接到电话 前来支援你
I got called out from the police station to support you.

517
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:51,230
波波利花园 上午 8:42
Boboli Gardens 8:42 AM

518
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:56,450
我需要更多帮手
I need more people.

519
00:39:03,710 --> 00:39:06,790
报告电台 发现嫌犯
Radio in, suspects found.

520
00:39:25,210 --> 00:39:28,630
该死的 四组 检查北边
Damn it! Delta, check the north perimeter.

521
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:32,640
这儿下去有扇灰色的小门
There's a small gray door down here.

522
00:39:32,660 --> 00:39:34,740
直通瓦萨里长廊
It will take us into the Vasari corridor.

523
00:39:34,770 --> 00:39:38,730
穿过维奇奥桥 就进到了宫里
Right across the Ponte Vecchio, and into the Palazzo.

524
00:39:38,750 --> 00:39:40,370
- 门在那 看 - 哦
- That's the door, see. - Yeah.

525
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:41,640
就现在
Now!

526
00:39:58,170 --> 00:39:59,920
花园是不是被墙整个围住的
Is the garden completely walled.

527
00:39:59,950 --> 00:40:01,290
四面全封闭
On all sides.

528
00:40:01,320 --> 00:40:04,430
唯一的出口要穿过北面的碧提宫
The only exits are through the Palazzo Pitti, on the north side,

529
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:07,080
或者通过东西两侧接待游客的大门
and through the visitors gates on the east and west sides.

530
00:40:07,100 --> 00:40:08,180
没有别的出路了
No other way out?

531
00:40:08,210 --> 00:40:10,340
如果瓦萨里长廊大门也算的话
I suppose if you count the Vasari gate.

532
00:40:10,370 --> 00:40:12,950
不过那门很老 鲜有人知
But it's ancient, no one knows about that.

533
00:40:12,970 --> 00:40:14,650
兰登知道
Langdon does.

534
00:40:22,860 --> 00:40:25,700
教授现在是个麻烦了 瓦任莎
The Professor has become a liability, Vayentha.

535
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:30,280
教务长已经发布了诛杀令 除掉兰登
The provost has issued a kill order. Eliminate Langdon.

536
00:40:30,300 --> 00:40:34,760
如若失败 你要负责 我说得够清楚了吗
Fail, and you will be held accountable. Am I making myself clear?

537
00:40:34,780 --> 00:40:36,660
明白了 长官
Copy that, sir.

538
00:40:50,100 --> 00:40:53,000
旧宫五百人大厅 早上 9:13

539
00:40:54,490 --> 00:40:55,530
那儿
There.

540
00:40:55,570 --> 00:40:59,470
瓦萨里的壁画 马西阿诺之战
That's the Vasari fresco, The Battle of Marciano.

541
00:41:38,700 --> 00:41:41,530
那儿 那儿 看 看 看 看
There. There. Look. Look, look, look.

542
00:41:42,380 --> 00:41:45,260
好的 看那两栋农舍 壁画中间往上
Okay, see the 2 farmhouses, dead center up high,

543
00:41:45,290 --> 00:41:47,020
往4点钟方向下移一点
come down to it's 4 o'clock,

544
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:49,640
你就看到一小面绿色战旗
and you'll see a small green flag.

545
00:41:49,670 --> 00:41:51,760
- Cerca trova - 对
- Cerca trova. - Yeah.

546
00:41:51,790 --> 00:41:53,070
寻找 就寻见
Seek and find.

547
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:55,950
寻找 就寻见
Seek and find.

548
00:41:55,970 --> 00:41:58,450
咱们看到了 找到了
We sought it and we found it.

549
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,450
那么 现在做什么
So, now what?

550
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:02,840
佐布里斯特加到画里的话
The words Zobrist added to the painting.

551
00:42:02,860 --> 00:42:06,780
唯有透过死亡之眼 才能瞥见真相
The truth can be glimpsed only through the eyes of death.

552
00:42:07,940 --> 00:42:09,660
死亡之眼
Eyes of death.

553
00:42:10,970 --> 00:42:12,810
谁的眼睛
Whose's eyes?

554
00:42:51,950 --> 00:42:53,910
我是不是被注射了什么东西
Was I given an injection?

555
00:42:53,940 --> 00:42:54,820
什么时候
When?

556
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:57,450
- 医院里面 颈动脉注射 - 没有
- At the hospital, with a hypertenol? - No.

557
00:42:57,480 --> 00:43:01,100
没有 你是插管输液治疗 只有静脉滴注
No, you were intubated. Anything you got came through the IV.

558
00:43:02,390 --> 00:43:04,410
不在医院里
Not at the hospital.

559
00:43:04,750 --> 00:43:08,100
我当时身着正装 在车厢后座上
I was fully dress. I was in the back of some car...

560
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:10,380
大概是过去两天里的某个时候
at some point in the last 2 days.

561
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:12,790
有东西注入了我的血液里
And something was injected into my bloodstream.

562
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:15,610
然后现在我开始外现临床病状
and now I'm showing signs of an illness

563
00:43:18,310 --> 00:43:19,790
会不会是...
What if...?

564
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,100
会是什么
What if what?

565
00:43:25,150 --> 00:43:27,550
西恩娜 我会不会就是携带者
Sienna, what if I'm the carrier?

566
00:43:29,090 --> 00:43:30,480
你看
Look.

567
00:43:31,550 --> 00:43:34,140
如果你携带了 那我也会被感染
If you've got it then I've got it too.

568
00:43:34,170 --> 00:43:38,000
还有我们接触过的每个人同样如此 都会死掉
And everyone we've come into contact with has it and will likely die.

569
00:43:38,020 --> 00:43:39,210
但如果并非如此
But if you don't.

570
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:43,680
如果 如果他们注射的是药剂或致幻剂 或者别的东西
If-If they gave you an anotic or a hallucinogen or anything else.

571
00:43:44,160 --> 00:43:47,360
那么我们仍有机会挽救这半个世界
Then we still have a chance to save half the world.

572
00:43:48,700 --> 00:43:50,890
值得一试 不是么
It's worth a try, isn't it?

573
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:01,310
教授
Professor.

574
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:06,640
啊 真是你 你怎么这么快就回来了
Ah, it is you. Why are you back so soon?

575
00:44:07,180 --> 00:44:09,640
我不知道她是谁
I have no idea who this woman is.

576
00:44:09,670 --> 00:44:14,080
你这身行头我差点没认出来 在逛街吗
I almost didn't recognize you in that suit. You've been shopping?

577
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:18,330
教授 你的头被撞了
Professor, you bumped your head.

578
00:44:18,350 --> 00:44:22,170
是的 洗澡的时候 暴跌一跤
In the shower, yes. It's quite a tumble.

579
00:44:22,190 --> 00:44:23,210
- 哎呀 - 嗯
- Ayes. - Yeah.

580
00:44:23,230 --> 00:44:27,300
打扰一下 这位是西恩娜 我的侄女
I'm sorry. This is Sienna, my niece.

581
00:44:27,330 --> 00:44:31,140
你人在意大利呢 教授 不必提这个
You're in Italy, Professor, you don't have to say 'niece'.

582
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:32,640
- 不是 不是的 - 不是的 他没有
- No. No. - No, he's not.

583
00:44:32,660 --> 00:44:36,990
你好 玛塔·阿尔瓦雷兹 很高兴见到你
Hello. Marta Alvarez. Pleasure to meet you.

584
00:44:37,210 --> 00:44:39,670
伊格纳奇奥(小主教座堂)也跟你一块来了吗
Is Ignazio with you again?

585
00:44:40,030 --> 00:44:42,480
- 伊格纳奇奥 - 对
- Ignazio? - Yeah.

586
00:44:51,290 --> 00:44:54,080
伊格纳奇奥今早没能成行
Ignazio couldn't make it this morning.

587
00:44:54,100 --> 00:44:58,200
很抱歉打搅你一下 玛塔 不过
I'm sorry to bother you, Marta. But...

588
00:44:58,230 --> 00:45:03,810
我想你大概能想到我为什么会在这里 又一次
I can imagine you know why I'm back. Again.

589
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:05,740
真的吗
Really?

590
00:45:06,050 --> 00:45:08,980
旧宫里头这么多的珍宝
Of all the treasures in the Palazzo.

591
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:13,430
昨天晚上他跟小主教座堂在那上面待了将近一个钟头
He and il Duomino spent almost an hour with it up there last night.

592
00:45:13,510 --> 00:45:16,450
真的 非同寻常
It's-It's so morbid.

593
00:45:16,470 --> 00:45:19,740
哪里哪里 这很正常
No. No. It's cool.

594
00:45:19,770 --> 00:45:23,390
好了 来吧 我来带路
Alright, come on. I'm headed up that way.

595
00:45:30,290 --> 00:45:32,520
他真是足智多谋的一个能人
He's an extremely resourceful man.

596
00:45:32,540 --> 00:45:35,580
我也对你说过这话 布沙尔先生
I was told you were as well, Mr. Bouchard.

597
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:41,150
那么 告诉我
So. Tell me.

598
00:45:41,160 --> 00:45:42,600
你觉得他在干嘛
What do you think he's doing?

599
00:45:42,620 --> 00:45:44,010
你觉得你在干嘛
What you think you doing?

600
00:45:44,030 --> 00:45:46,230
我把指示器带给你 现在它没了
I brought you the pointer and now it's gone.

601
00:45:46,250 --> 00:45:48,460
- 你弄丢了 - 我们在街上跟丢了他
- You have a leak. - We losed him in the street.

602
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:50,480
在医生的住处又重新发现了
Reacquired him at the doctor's apartment.

603
00:45:50,500 --> 00:45:52,190
有大家支持 我还能掌控
I can handle with some ground.

604
00:45:52,220 --> 00:45:54,880
- 我们不需要你帮忙 - 如果他受伤了
- We don't need your help. - What if he's injured.

605
00:45:56,140 --> 00:45:57,880
头部受创
A head wound.

606
00:45:58,120 --> 00:45:59,470
什么意思 你认为他糊涂了
What? You think he's confused.

607
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:02,080
- 他不知道他在干嘛吗 - 有可能
- He doesn't know what he's doing? - It's possible.

608
00:46:02,110 --> 00:46:05,620
他晚上失踪前进展到了哪里
How far did he get the night before he disappeared?

609
00:46:05,650 --> 00:46:07,750
五百人大厅
To the Hall of Five Hundred.

610
00:46:09,310 --> 00:46:11,310
那我们就不追了
So let's stop chasing him,

611
00:46:11,810 --> 00:46:14,090
提前守着他
anticipate him instead.

612
00:46:26,060 --> 00:46:29,230
嘿 朋友 还请悠着点
Whoa, inspector. Not so fast, please.

613
00:46:29,300 --> 00:46:31,410
我快燃起来了
I'm about to burst.

614
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:34,660
这么浪漫的一天 他却带你来欣赏死亡面具
Such a romantic date he takes you on. To see a death mask.

615
00:46:34,680 --> 00:46:37,370
是的 在16世纪 它们相当普遍
Yeah, they were common practice in the 1500s.

616
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:41,360
实质上就是某个人面部的石膏模型
It's essentially just a plaster cast of someone's face,

617
00:46:41,380 --> 00:46:44,650
在其死后不久套模浇注的
made a few moments after that person dies.

618
00:46:44,960 --> 00:46:46,570
"透过死亡之眼"
"Through the eyes of death."

619
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:50,700
这幅面具的模型 是一位诗人
The person who was used for this mask, the poet,

620
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,770
叫但丁
Dante.

621
00:46:54,240 --> 00:46:56,780
我想这是一个浪漫的故事
It is a romantic story I supposed.

622
00:46:56,800 --> 00:47:00,760
但丁热爱这座城市 他在当时很显赫 又有影响力 但
Dante loved Florence, he was prominent and powerful. But...

623
00:47:00,780 --> 00:47:03,650
在政治权力更迭后 他被罢黜流放
The political winds changed and he was exiled.

624
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:06,950
人们威胁他 若胆敢回来 就火刑伺候
They threatened to burn him at the stake if he ever returned.

625
00:47:06,970 --> 00:47:13,140
实际上 有人认为对但丁的放逐 是面具看着如此悲恸的原因
Actually, some people say Dante's exile is the reason his death mask looks so sad.

626
00:47:13,180 --> 00:47:17,260
不 不对 那是因为比阿特丽斯的原因 ("神曲"中的人物)
No. No. It was because of Beatrice.

627
00:47:17,290 --> 00:47:21,620
但丁只从远处见过她 但她却被其终生迷恋
Dante only knew her from afar but he was obsessed with her his entire life.

628
00:47:22,070 --> 00:47:24,990
你的侄女很浪漫呢 教授
Your niece is a romantic, Professor.

629
00:47:25,350 --> 00:47:30,300
人们认为 但丁所撰的穿越地狱之行 实际上是为了找到她
They say Dante wrote in fact about his journey out of hell to reach her.

630
00:47:30,340 --> 00:47:32,300
但他没能成功
But he never made it.

631
00:47:33,020 --> 00:47:35,310
她已嫁给另主
She married someone else.

632
00:47:35,410 --> 00:47:37,330
这事常常发生
That happens.

633
00:47:37,350 --> 00:47:38,800
有吗
Does it?

634
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:40,960
谁撇下了谁
Who left who?

635
00:47:40,990 --> 00:47:43,770
有些东西 若你不加以照料 就会难以为继
Things fall apart if you don't look after them.

636
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:47,260
噢 馆方要求 参观时你们只能站在立柱外
Oh. We ask that you stay behind the stanchions. Please.

637
00:47:47,290 --> 00:47:48,130
谢谢
Thank you.

638
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:51,270
来得很巧 教授 我们刚刚开门
Good timing, Professor. We've only just opened.

639
00:47:55,910 --> 00:47:57,090
玛塔...
Marta...

640
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:58,630
在
Yes?

641
00:48:33,750 --> 00:48:35,440
那儿 那是我们
There. That's us.

642
00:48:39,360 --> 00:48:41,430
那是伊格纳奇奥·布索尼 ("小主教座堂")
That's Ignazio Busoni.

643
00:48:41,670 --> 00:48:43,050
我们相识多年
I've known him for years.

644
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:45,460
他是研究但丁的学者
He's the Dante scholar.

645
00:48:47,060 --> 00:48:51,200
面具的主人坚持要求参观者要站在立柱之外
The mask's owner insists on the stanchions to keep people back.

646
00:48:51,230 --> 00:48:54,470
未经许可 工作人员也不能打开展柜
He doesn't even permit staff to open the case without him present.

647
00:48:54,490 --> 00:48:57,390
所以面具不是博物馆所有
So the mask is not owned by the museum?

648
00:48:57,410 --> 00:48:59,430
不是 有位私人收藏家从我们手里买下了
No. A private collector bought it from us,

649
00:48:59,460 --> 00:49:01,780
并允许我们做永久性展览
and allows us to display it in perpetuity.

650
00:49:01,810 --> 00:49:05,480
这是筹集经费的惯常做法
It's a common practice, to raise funds.

651
00:49:06,100 --> 00:49:07,360
他是何许人也
Who is the collector?

652
00:49:07,380 --> 00:49:10,850
贝特朗·佐布里斯特 那位亿万富翁
Bertram Zobrist, the billionaire.

653
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:15,800
他的观点很古怪 但其自杀之事仍旧令人遗憾
His ideas were quite eccentric, but still it's such a shame what happened.

654
00:49:16,840 --> 00:49:18,850
那就是我接电话的时候了
That's when I got the call.

655
00:49:47,200 --> 00:49:48,510
喔
Oh.

656
00:49:48,730 --> 00:49:51,910
教授 我 我不知道该作何感想
Professor, I... I don't know what to think!

657
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:54,220
我很震惊
I am appalled!

658
00:50:04,870 --> 00:50:07,270
- 教授 - 兰登教授
- Professor. - Professor Langdon.

659
00:50:07,290 --> 00:50:10,540
瞧 这事情肯定有个解释
Look. There's an explanation for all this.

660
00:50:12,040 --> 00:50:15,000
警察来了 警铃响了
The police came and the alarm went off.

661
00:50:15,300 --> 00:50:16,500
这些都是什么人
Who are they?

662
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:18,100
他们都是特工人员
They're government agents.

663
00:50:20,180 --> 00:50:21,700
你有客人了
You have an intruder.

664
00:50:22,970 --> 00:50:24,180
我马上回来
I'll be right back.

665
00:50:24,200 --> 00:50:26,680
玛塔 别让他俩跑了
Marta, don't let them go.

666
00:50:28,950 --> 00:50:31,300
你不能带枪进这来
You can not bring a gun here.

667
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:45,860
教授
Professor.

668
00:50:45,890 --> 00:50:49,800
教授 我非常尊敬您 但我不明白
Professor, I very much respect you but I do not understand.

669
00:50:49,830 --> 00:50:51,990
- 请坐 我会解释 - 你为什么做这事
- Please sit down. I'm going to explain this. - Why you have done this?

670
00:50:52,020 --> 00:50:54,820
- 那可不行 - 玛塔 我不知道面具在哪儿
- This is not okay. - Marta, I do not know where the mask is.

671
00:50:54,850 --> 00:50:57,590
但我会竭尽全力找到它 还给你们
But I will do everything I can to find it and return it to you.

672
00:50:57,620 --> 00:51:00,590
教授 你在干嘛 教授 求你 不要
Professor, what are you doing? Professor, please. No.

673
00:51:00,610 --> 00:51:03,070
教授 回来 别这样
Professor, come back. Don't do that.

674
00:51:03,100 --> 00:51:04,470
教授 请不要
Professor, please don't.

675
00:51:04,500 --> 00:51:05,590
- 嘿 嘿 - 教授
- Hey. Hey. - Professor.

676
00:51:05,620 --> 00:51:08,810
- 你别跟着就好 - 求你了 别这样
- Just don't follow us. - Please, don't do this.

677
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:12,430
教授
Professor!

678
00:51:20,480 --> 00:51:23,360
咱们偷偷找条路子离开这儿
Let's just calmly find a way out of here.

679
00:51:28,230 --> 00:51:30,960
你为什么不告诉我伊格纳奇奥的事情
Why didn't you tell me about Ignazio?

680
00:51:31,240 --> 00:51:33,590
如果你知道我是个贼 你还会帮我吗
Would you help me if you knew I was a thief?

681
00:51:33,610 --> 00:51:35,210
你向我求助的时候撒了谎
You lied to me when you asked for my help.

682
00:51:35,240 --> 00:51:37,410
对 严格说来 我有所保留
Well technically, I withheld.

683
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:42,350
如果我真的拿了那副面具...
If I really took that mask...

684
00:51:42,380 --> 00:51:44,000
你的确拿了 我刚刚才看到
You did take the mask, I just saw you.

685
00:51:44,020 --> 00:51:47,640
这不是你的问题 你不必跟着
This is not your problem. You don't have to stay.

686
00:51:47,660 --> 00:51:50,860
我当然要陪着 人类正面临生死存亡
Of course, I do. Human lives are at stake.

687
00:51:50,890 --> 00:51:52,620
我只想知道我没站错队
I just want to know that I'm on the right side.

688
00:51:52,650 --> 00:51:54,020
你没有
You are.

689
00:51:54,650 --> 00:51:56,260
我发誓
I swear.

690
00:51:56,440 --> 00:51:57,770
好的
Good.

691
00:51:58,210 --> 00:52:00,610
